In 2010, the racial makeup of the town was 54.99% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 44.18% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.56% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.28% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.77% of the population. In 2020, the racial makeup was 70.57% African American, 25.64% non-Hispanic white, 0.33% Native American, 1.56% other or mixed, and 1.78% Hispanic or Latino of any race.<ref name=":0" />

